12/08/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The Greek Foreign Ministry's International Development Co-operation Agency -- Hellenic Aid -- announced the approval of 50,000 euros in aid for the residents of flooded regions in Bulgaria on Wednesday (10 August). 
The aid was signed by Greek Deputy Foreign Minister Evripidis Stylianidis, and will be used to purchase blankets, clothing, water pumps, food items and drinking water. 
(ANA, MPA - 10/08/05)
